      • countByTenantId

        @Query("SELECT count(*) FROM DeviceEntity d WHERE d.tenantId = :tenantId")
java.lang.Long countByTenantId​(@Param("tenantId")
                               java.util.UUID tenantId)
        Count devices by tenantId. Custom query applied because default QueryDSL produces slow count(id).

        There is two way to count devices. OPTIMAL: count(*) - returns _row_count_ and use index-only scan (super fast). SLOW: count(id) - returns _NON_NULL_id_count and performs table scan to verify isNull for each id in filtered rows.
